Constructor Detail

Fragment

public Fragment(String line)
Create a fragment from a string. Note that the string must denote internal nodes with asterisks, or the fragment will parse as just the top level. For example, the following two lines will create identical fragments: Fragment f = new Fragment("(S NP VP)"); Fragment f = new Fragment("(S NP (VP (VBD said) NP))"); The following line gives a large fragment with the expected predicate argument structure: Fragment f = new Fragment("(S NP (*VP (*VBD said) NP))");
